  "keyFeatures": [
    "4x to 10x faster than strtod and standard library from_chars",
    "Header-only, zero allocations, no exceptions",
    "Exact IEEE 754 rounding (round-to-even)",
    "Supports float, double, fixed-width types (float16_t, bfloat16_t), and integers",
    "C++11 compatible with optional C++20 constexpr support",
    "UTF-8, UTF-16, and UTF-32 input support",
    "Custom decimal separators, JSON, and Fortran format modes",
    "Cross-platform: Linux, macOS, Windows, FreeBSD; little and big endian"
  ],
